<HR size="1" color="#12350C">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif">
Greetings Everyone,<P>OOC<P>I have been content to be a lurker on this board for some time.  While I agree with you on many of the problems of the class (especially POST 30 it takes a huge nosedive..I am 35 now) I thought the eventual fixing of the pet runspeed bug as well as further charm availability would solve my two main gripes.  Of course, then the mez random duration came along which we all agree was a nasty blow and since everyone was making such a fuss already I felt I did not need to add my voice.<P>But now the matter improvement.  It is wonderful that the line will finally be made viable.  It was what I wanted to 2/3 spec along with mind from the beginning (because I love dots), but it was so weak compared to body that it seemed just too poor a path to take.  Especially since at that time Body had the old Dex/quick debuff which was arguably our best spell.<P>Now we hear that matter will be made viable as well as becoming an excellent RvR line.  Well of course since I play this game for Roleplaying and RvR, a mind/matter sorcerer is exactly what I want and have been wanting since I first started playing.<P>I just assumed that if any sweeping changes were made to a class after people had devoted a lot of time to it, spec points would be made redistributable.  So if matter was ever made viable, I would get a chance to redesign my sorcerer.  But I have heard some voices here that seem to say 'too bad'.  Had I known either A) Matter was going to be improved or B)We would not be able to respec whether it was or wasnt improved, I would have saved my points. But Matter being improved and not being able to respec... <P>This is every bit as bad as a character wipe.<P>I am a easy going person.  I happily embrace all the necessary changes that go on in such games even if it makes me weaker.  It is very tricky to balance all these competing factors and I have endless patience for Mythic in doing so.<P>But if I play a class that was not finished to start with, then it suddenly becomes 'finished' much later in development, should I not get the same freedom to choose my strengths and weaknesses as a new beginner to that class would?<P>I just cannot believe that those of us who started early will be penalized into a much narrower frame of possiblity than those who start later.  We are the ones suffering through and bringing attention to the problems that will make the class more fun in the future for everyone, yet we will be penalized for this in having to throw out our characters if we are more attracted to the new abilities?<P>I heard RvR charm was not allowed because Mythic wanted to protect players from the horrible experience of 'losing control'.<P>Well how does losing control once in a while in battling the foe even begin to compare with losing control of everything you have worked for in your character?<P>From the balance perspective as a Body/Mind sorcerer I will be just as powerful as the new Mind/Matter Sorcerer so Ellejienne is 'fine'.<P>But the truth is Ellejienne will be dead. Its the same as a player wipe for me. I could not stand playing a Mind/Body Sorcerer knowing that Mind/Matter is really my niche.<P>And I also could not bear to redo 35 levels of the same character.<P>Be a sad end to a fun game and many fine friends I have made.<P>Ellejienne DeGales of Percival
</FONT>
