<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif">
This is not a flame or argument and I hope I don't offend anybody. Just a thought:<P>Sorcerers who started playing since beta or even during the early release days had an advantage new sorcerers don't.<P>That is the pre-nerf advantage. I heard that, then, debuffs were so uber that mobs can't even hit you anymore. And resist didn't exist. And mez was reliable. <P>So those players had a slightly easier time to level than sorcerers of today and took a shorter time, and they still get to keep their characters. <P>So I think it's fair that new sorcerers now get an "advantage" that older ones don't? The only ones getting the wrong end of the stick are those who came in between - we don't get anything. (I started the game around the time mez was nerfed, but I'm lvl 36 now and too late to respec if they revamp matter).<P>Well, someone correct me if I'm wrong.  <IMG SRC="smile.gif" border="0">
