<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif">
Well somewhat true I think, though the ones to get the 'advantage' you speak of were very few indeed, most of whom seem to have quit for one reason or another.  The super powered dex debuff was good at lower levels but hardly overpowering until high levels where it could send a creatures chance to hit into the negatives.<P>In any case, who had more advantage thus might be more deserving is at most a secondary issue. (I started early but have not been able to play much till recently, so am in the same boat as you.)<P>Main issue being the class was unfinished making pretty much one obvious spec path only. Now it will be balanced to have several interesting options, should not that be open to everyone?<P>I did not really want to spec body, but I wanted an effective sorcerer and matter was clumsily designed.  So I must lose all my work because the design was poor?<P>If matter was viable from the beginning then of course respeccing should not be an option. One made one choice knowing the facts.<P>But in our case there facts were not known, therefore we should get a fresh start now that they will be known.<P>PS By 'finished' I do not mean the class is final. Obviously it will never be and will always be improved.  I simply mean by finished a class that has several viable ways of operating depending upon the skills chosen.  Many of the classes were finished at release, many were not.<P>Sorceres were workable, but not finished.
