<HR size="1" color="#12350C">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif">
Just here to add a couple of things:<P>1) I fully support Ellejienne's post.<P>2) Ellejienne said that he might have "saved up" his points if he'd known about the potential for such a major change.  The problem with this is that, for caster classes, "saving" points is simply not a viable strategy.  Unlike a polearm armsman, who can "bank" skill points to take advantage of auto-train, we only receive 1X points per level, and by saving those points we would be significantly disadvantaged - we'd access to specialty spells and be relying on weaker base spells as we play.  Moreover, why should you HAVE to sacrifice your enjoyment for the fear that a major change will later occur that makes your character strategy less than desireable?<P>3) In response to Sheylara's post about the perceived "advantages" that the sorceror has had in the past as a justification for NOT allowing re-specs, I have several comments:<P>  a) This works both ways.  There may have been some advantages early on, but there have also been things added later in the game that have made it easier to be a mage, most significantly bladeturn.  So, turning your logic around, because we were not entitled to this "advantage" from the start don't we deserve compensation now?<P>  b) The dex debuff "exploit" was really confined to players who used the matter line dex debuff (and stacked it).  At higher levels the combo debuff itself may have offered a significant advantage, but I don't think that most sorcerors leveled fast enough to take advantage of it -- and I as I said I think it was only the matter line dex debuff that really offered the advantage.  I used the combo debuff as I leveled, and I was never able to solo reds -- I could solo oranges without having to change out my pet as often, but that was all.<P>  c) The resistance changes that I think you're referring to were on debuffs.  They fixed this very soon after release -- October 23, patch 1.33 -- so it really wasn't around long.  Again, it didn't offer a significant advantage to players, because they were all fairly low level anyway, and it may have allowed for soloing multiple oranges without trading in your pet but not really high stuff.<P>  d) These changes that you mention actually further justify allowing a re-spec.  Suppose, for example, you rolled up your character thinking that debuffs were not supposed to be resisted?  Or suppose you went full mind spec and then the durations of mez got nerfed?  Either way, you deserve the opportunity to re-allocate points in the light of these significant changes.<P>Anyway, there's my thoughts on the "matter."  Hehehee, little pun there  <IMG SRC="smile.gif" border="0"><P>--------------------<P>--Kestrel Trebor, Sorceror<BR>The Sacred Brotherhood<BR>"Honor, loyalty, and above all, brotherhood!"<BR>Albion, Percival Server
</FONT>
