<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif">
when major overhauls like this have happened in BETA, they did a complete spec reset for ALL of the class affected. You then had to revisit your guild and train as you wished. If you wanted to redo what you had, great. If not, also fine.<P>2 things factor into this however.<P>If you wipe a class that gets free specs in skills, they are now getting bonus points they did not have before. If an armsman neglects certain skills, he may automatically get one train every 5 levels. If it is ne of his chosen weapon he never gets those. It is intended to keep some skills from bing completely neglected. Now if he was 25 and had his points wiped, he now gets 5 free spec points in that line, and it completely changes his point totals.<P>Not a big deal. Some thing those auto train points should come from his training pool, and others think that they shoudl get them free even if they HAVE trained that skill. Either way, this is a concern.<P>But not for casters.<P>We do have to consider anotehr thing here also. If you are level 36 and have not trained matter since level 1, you will feel cheated. But what happens if you hit level 37? You now have 37 points to spend. this will immediately take you to level 8 in this skill. By next level you can have this almost to level 12. So you CAN get to the 1/2 spec that makes a secondary line useful in only 3 levels. this is not so bad.<P>the only people this would directly hit are those who want to change their enire path to matter. Those people really should play it form the gorupnd up as it is actually an entirely different class in this case, and you woudl want to develop the skills neccessary to be effective at it. Many will only do this to jump on he "LeeT PvPer" bandwagon. most will be happy to allow the new spells to accent the mind spec sorceror they enjoy playing already.<P>And as for the benefits of the BETA players. there was a complete wipe on Pendragon when BETA 4 started, and it has not been wiped since. This has NO bearing on any characters on the live servers. from day one we have had the same limitations as anyone else.<P>I can almost guarantee that a spec point reset will take place on test. But they may or may not do this on live for many reasons, a few of which i have listed here.<P>--------------------<P>i3ullseye<BR>"You're good, but me? I'm Magic!"<P>Rictus -Sorceror(DAOC)/Rictus(EQ)<BR>DAOC Sorceror team lead...<P>Please visit our <A HREF="http://www.yesterdayland.com/popopedia/shows/toys/ty1050.php" TARGET=_blank>Sponsors!</A>  <IMG SRC="biggrin.gif" border="0">
