Hummm.....I think I agree with the idea that it would indeed be a bit improbable to ask for us to redistribute our specialization points.  Might be sensible, but probably too much trouble.<P>The way I see it as this:  The Matter line should never, ever be THE difinitive RvR line.  No line should *ever* be that.  Because each line should add something definately useful to RvR.  Depending on when and how they're used, all three lines *should* offer something useful in RvR.  That is what they mean by "different styles of play", that being that none is better than the other, but each offers a unique playsyle (compared to the others) that they all have their uses and weaknesses.<P>~Sigma<BR>26 Sorcerer<BR>Percival
